    "long_instructions": ">This is an example of an investigate and modify level from PRIMM. \r\n\r\n## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Run the code and observe.\r\n2. *Consider: The `Painter` passed over a paint bucket. What do you think its purpose is?*\r\n3. Uncomment (delete the `#`'s) the code on lines 13-15, 18, 20, and 22. Then run the program. \r\n4. *Reflect:* \r\n\t- *Was your prediction about the bucket accurate?*\r\n    - *What does the number on the bucket represent?*\r\n5. Paint a yellow line to the cone.\r\n\r\n See the <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1x3xmKI_ADq8GaGoI0XGX9pJIE4VmPM3iXq_qIHeo7r4/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">documentation</a>\r\nfor how to change the color of the paint.    \r\n\r\n*While in the documentation, take a look at all of the color names you can use.*\r\n    \r\n::: details [**🔎 Show me how**]\r\n![](https://images.code.org/533eaea72cc0d264feca43dc27c605da-image-1743174839405.png)\r\n:::\r\n\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\nzoe = Painter()\n\nzoe.move()\nzoe.move()\nzoe.move()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.move()\n\n#zoe.take_paint()\n#zoe.take_paint()\n#zoe.take_paint()\n\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
